Url%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Two%20women%20partially%20buried%20in%20gravel%20during%20protest%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721576677000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-111907468%2Cimgsize-894213.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Ftwo-women-partially-buried-in-gravel-during-protest-in-madhya-pradesh%2Farticleshow%2F111907405.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20NEWS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Ftwo-women-partially-buried-in-gravel-during-protest-in-madhya-pradesh%2Farticleshow%2F111907405.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%223%20BJP%20Allies%20Question%20UP%20Order%20To%20Eateries%20For%20Kanwar%20Yatra%2C%20Want%20Rollback%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20dissent%20against%20the%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20government's%20order%20to%20eateries%20to%20display%20names%20of%20owners%20during%20kanwar%20yatra%20has%20spread%20to%20the%20ruling%20alliance.%20Two%20Union%20ministers%20who%20are%20BJP%20allies%20have%20appealed%20to%20the%20state%20to%20roll%20back%20its%20decision.%20A%20third%20party%2C%20Nitish%20Kumar's%20Janata%20Dal%20United%2C%20has%20also%20criticised%20the%20order%2C%20calling%20it%20an%20example%20of%20discrimination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Lok%20Janshakti%20Party%20chief%20Chirag%20Paswan%20--%20who%20handles%20the%20Food%20Processing%20industries%20portfolio%20at%20the%20Centre%20--%20Rashtriya%20Lok%20Dal%20chief%20Jayant%20Chaudhary%20today%20said%20kanwariyas%20ask%20no-one%20their%20religion%20when%20they%20seek%20service.%20Neither%20should%20the%20matter%20(serving%20kanwariyas)%20be%20linked%20to%20any%20religion%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20seems%20that%20the%20order%20was%20taken%20without%20much%20thought%20and%20the%20government%20is%20adamant%20on%20it%20because%20the%20decision%20has%20been%20taken%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Chaudhary%20--%20junior%20minister%20for%20education%20who%20has%20independent%20charge%20of%20skill%20development%20--%20was%20quoted%20as%20saying%20by%20news%20agency%20Press%20Trust%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20still%20time.%20It%20(roll%20back)%20should%20happen%20or%20the%20government%20should%20not%20put%20much%20emphasis%20on%20(implementing)%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Chaudhary%20also%20questioned%20if%20one%20should%20wear%20a%20name%20tag%20on%20one's%20clothes%20to%20identify%20one's%20religion.%20%26quot%3BWhere%20all%20one%20would%20be%20made%20to%20place%20these%20identifiers!%20Should%20we%20now%20wear%20name%20tags%20too%3F%20So%20that%20one%20knows%20who%20to%20shake%20hands%20with%3F%26quot%3B%20said%20Mr%20Chaudhary%2C%20whose%20party%20has%20its%20stronghold%20in%20western%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20Union%20minister%20Chirag%20Paswan%20had%20unequivocally%20opposed%20the%20order%2C%20saying%20he%20would%20%26quot%3Babsolutely%E2%80%A6%20never%20support%20or%20encourage%26quot%3B%20any%20divide%20in%20the%20name%20of%20caste%20or%20religion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20BJP%20ally%2C%20Nitish%20Kumar's%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%2C%20has%20also%20criticised%20the%20move.%20Party%20leader%20KC%20Tyagi%20has%20said%20the%20order%20should%20be%20withdrawn%20as%20it%20may%20cause%20communal%20tension.%20There%20should%20be%20no%20discrimination%20based%20on%20religion%20or%20caste%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Muzaffarnagar%20Police%20order%20to%20eateries%20along%20the%20Kanwar%20Yatra%20route%20to%20display%20owners'%20names%2C%20has%20now%20been%20extended%20across%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20and%20Uttarakhand.%20The%20order%20has%20been%20hugely%20criticised%20by%20the%20Opposition%20parties%2C%20who%20maintain%20it%20targets%20Muslim%20traders.%