n%3Cp%3ENo%20mention%20of%20caste-based%20discrimination%2C%20tweaks%20in%20references%20to%20B%20R%20Ambedkar's%20experience%20about%20the%20discrimination%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20Harappan%20civilisation%20as%20%26quot%3BSindhu-Sarasvati%26quot%3B%20are%20also%20among%20the%20changes%20in%20the%20textbook%20developed%20according%20to%20a%20new%20curriculum.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Greenwich%20Meridian%20is%20not%20the%20first%20prime%20meridian.%20There%20were%20others%20in%20the%20past.%20In%20fact%2C%20many%20centuries%20before%20Europe%2C%20India%20had%20a%20prime%20meridian%20of%20its%20own!%20It%20was%20called%20madhya%20rekh%C4%81%20(or%20'middle%20line')%20and%20passed%20through%20the%20city%20of%20Ujjayin%C4%AB%20(today%20Ujjain)%2C%20which%20was%20a%20reputed%20centre%20for%20astronomy%20over%20many%20centuries.%20%26quot%3BVar%C4%81hamihira%2C%20a%20famous%20astronomer%2C%20lived%20and%20worked%20there%20some%201%2C500%20years%20ago.%20Indian%20astronomers%20were%20aware%20of%20the%20concepts%20of%20latitude%20and%20longitude%2C%20including%20the%20need%20for%20a%20zero%20or%20prime%20meridian.%20The%20Ujjayin%C4%AB%20meridian%20became%20a%20reference%20for%20calculations%20in%20all%20Indian%20astronomical%20texts%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20textbook%20reads.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20departure%20from%20the%20past%2C%20the%20textbook%20makes%20multiple%20references%20to%20the%20%26quot%3BSarasvati%26quot%3B%20river%20in%20the%20chapter%20pertaining%20to%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20Indian%20civilisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20new%20textbook%2C%20the%20river%20finds%20a%20prominent%20place%20in%20a%20chapter%20on%20the%20%26quot%3BBeginnings%20of%20Indian%20Civilisation%26quot%3B%2C%20where%20the%20Harappan%20civilisation%20is%20referred%20to%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BIndus-Sarasvati%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BSindhu-Sarasvati%26quot%3B%20civilisation.%20It%20says%20the%20%26quot%3BSarasvati%26quot%3B%20basin%20included%20major%20cities%20of%20the%20civilisation%20--%20Rakhigarhi%20and%20Ganweriwala%20--%20along%20with%20smaller%20cities%20and%20towns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20river%2C%20according%20to%20the%20new%20textbook%2C%20%26quot%3Btoday%20goes%20by%20the%20name%20of%20'Ghaggar'%20in%20India%20and%20'Hakra'%20in%20Pakistan%20(hence%20the%20name%20'Ghaggar-Hakra%20River')%26quot%3B%20and%20is%20now%20seasonal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20textbook%2C%20titled%20%26quot%3BExploring%20Society%20India%20and%20Beyond%26quot%3B%2C%20has%20details%20on%20the%20Vedas%20without%20mentioning%20the%20caste%20system%20and%20that%20women%20and%20Shudras%20were%20not%20allowed%20to%20study%20these%20scriptures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20new%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BMany%20professions%20are%20mentioned%20in%20the%20vedic%20texts%2C%20such%20as%20agriculturist%2C%20weaver%2C%20potter%2C%20builder%2C%20carpenter%2C%20healer%2C%20dancer%2C%20barber%2C%20priest%2C%20etc.%26quot%3B%20The%20previous%20textbook%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BSome%20priests%20divided%20people%20into%20four%20groups%20called%20varnas....%20Shudras%20could%20not%20perform%20any%20rituals.%20Often%20women%20were%20grouped%20with%20Shudras.%20Both%20women%20and%20Shudras%20were%20not%20allowed%20to%20study%20the%20Vedas.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BThe%20priests%20also%20said%20that%20these%20groups%20were%20decided%20based%20on%20birth.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20one's%20father%20and%20mother%20were%20Brahmins%2C%20one%20would%20automatically%20become%20a%20Brahmin%20and%20so%20on...%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20old%20book%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20references%20were%20also%20tweaked%20in%20the%20COVID-19%20rationalisation%2C%20which%20was%20earlier%20termed%20temporary%20by%20the%20NCERT%20to%20reduce%20burden.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20social%20science%20textbook%20for%20Class%206%20is%20a%20heavily-truncated%20amalgamation%20of%20what%20were%20earlier%20three%20separate%20books%20for%20history%2C%20geography%20and%20civics%20published%20by%20the%20National%20Council%20of%20Educational%20Research%20and%20Training%20(NCERT).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20tried%20to%20keep%20the%20text%20to%20a%20minimum%20by%20focusing%20on%20the%20'big%20ideas'.%20This%20has%20enabled%20us%20to%20combine%20in%20a%20single%20theme%20inputs%20from%20several%20disciplines%20--%20whether%20history%2C%20geography%2C%20political%20science%20or%20economics%2C%26quot%3B%20NCERT%20Director%20Dinesh%20Saklani%20writes%20in%20the%20introductory%20chapter%20of%20the%20new%20textbook.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20has%20been%20culled%20drastically%20is%20the%20detailed%20exploration%20of%20the%20kingdoms%20of%20ancient%20India%2C%20such%20as%20those%20contained%20in%20four%20chapters%20of%20the%20old%20book%20that%20have%20been%20deleted%20from%20the%20new.%20This%20includes%20accounts%20of%20the%20kingdoms%20of%20Ashoka%20and%20Chandragupta%20Maurya%2C%20including%20the%20role%20of%20Chanakya%20and%20his%20Arthashastra%20as%20well%20as%20the%20dynasties%20of%20the%20Guptas%2C%20Pallavas%20and%20Chalukyas%2C%20and%20the%20work%20of%20Kalidasa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20the%20only%20mention%20of%20King%20Ashoka%20in%20the%20entire%20book%20is%20a%20single%20word%20in%20the%20fourth%20chapter's%20timeline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20chapter%20in%20the%20old%20book%20on%20%26quot%3BVillages%2C%20Towns%20and%20Trade%26quot%3B%20about%20the%20tools%2C%20coins%2C%20irrigation%2C%20crafts%20and%20trade%20of%20the%20period%20has%20been%20truncated.%20References%20to%20the%20famed%20iron%20pillar%20at%20the%20Qutub%20Minar%20site%20at%20Delhi's%20Mehrauli%2C%20which%20probably%20dates%20back%20to%20the%20Gupta%20dynasty%20era%2C%20have%20been%20dropped%2C%20along%20with%20mentions%20of%20the%20Sanchi%20Stupa%2C%20the%20monolithic%20temples%20of%20Mahabalipuram%20and%20the%20paintings%20in%20the%20Ajanta%20caves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20